      • fromExt

        public static <T> T fromExt(org.gradle.api.Project project,
                            java.lang.String keyName,
                            java.util.function.Function<T,T> transformer,
                            java.util.function.Supplier<T> creator)
        Gets a value from the project's "extra properties", creating and/or transforming it.

        If the key does not currently exist in "extra properties", the creator is called to create a new instance.

        Regardless of if the value was found or newly created, the transformer is always called upon it and the result put back into "extra properties" before being returned from this method. Therefore it is important that transformer is idempotent.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value
        Parameters:
        project - the project containing the "extra properties"
        keyName - the property name
        transformer - the IDEMPOTENT value transformer
        creator - the supplier of new value instances
        See Also:
        setFromExt(Project, String, Supplier)

      • compareMaps

        public static <K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>,V extends java.lang.Comparable<V>> int compareMaps(java.util.Map<K,V> m1,
                                                                                                    java.util.Map<K,V> m2)
        Compares two Maps of Comparable items. If one is null, that sorts lower. If one's size is smaller, that sorts lower. Otherwise the keys are compared. (See compareSets(Set, Set).) If the keys are the same, the first difference in the values found when searching the sorted keys is used for the comparision.
        See Also:
        Comparable

      • compareSets

        public static <U extends java.lang.Comparable<U>> int compareSets(java.util.Set<U> s1,
                                                                  java.util.Set<U> s2)
        Compares two Sets of Comparable items. If one is null, that sorts lower. If one's size is smaller, that sorts lower. Otherwise the first non-equal value after they are sorted is used for the comparision.
        See Also:
        Comparable
